      • getRoad

        public Road getRoad()
        Road to which this node belongs to.

        Notice that the road is automatically set by the OsmArcsBuilder. However, for nodes representing the junction between two roads, which road is associated to the node is uncertain, because it depends on the order in which roads are read.

        However, the road associated to an arc is unambiguous, so use arcs instead if it's really important. Arcs can be accessed through Node.getIncomingArcs(), Node.getOutgoingArcs(), or event from Plan.getCurrentArc().

        Returns:
        osm road associated to this node
